channel.title: Should I be worried?
channel.description: Ok so the problem is I downloaded a source+client and when I did google chrome said it was malicious but I used it before on a different computer and there was no problem. So just to be sure I scanned it and there was no threat found. I checked all the runs/compilers before I ran any of it and I still found nothing. After awhile I still found nothing but I am just wondering is it ok to still be using it even though google chrome said that it might be malicious??

item.title: Should I be worried?
item.dc:creator: @drubrkletern drubrkletern
item.description:
@drubrkletern wrote:

i want fire:

Guys before I did anything with it I scanned it to see if anything was going to harm me and I found nothing. So I check ALL THE RUNS AND COMPILERS before I ran them and nothing out of the ordinary happened. I had this before when playing peoples private servers because for some reason that happens and I was just wondering why. But I deleted everything having to do with it and I scanned it again and I found no threats at all and the reason I gave up so quickly I just wanted to be safe. I had the source and client for like a month and nothing bad has happened. I got my friend to download it as well and he said he couldn’t find anything that could harm me but he said that when he plays peoples private servers sometimes the same thing pops up when you download something on google chrome.

chrome is the problem kill it im telling you
